   <head>❧ The Argument of the Dialogue.</head>
   <p>TWo learned men Gentlemen, met by chaūce, the one of them speaketh much euill of Phisi<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tions: and holdeth opiniō, that nei<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ther Phisition, nor Arte of medi<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>cine ought to be, but y<seg rend="sup">t</seg> men should be cured with vse and experience. The other doth commend also and defend, bothe Medicine &amp; Phisiti<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ons. And last of all, the matter is decided by a learned man, called Maister <hi>Velasques,</hi> verie notably.</p>
   <trailer>FINIS.</trailer>
